## Animation details

### 1. Headline — clip-path line reveal (each line)
Wrap every line in `<span class={lineWrap}>` (overflow hidden) containing `<span class={lineInner}>`. GSAP animates `y: '110%'→0` per inner span with stagger 0.12s.

```js
gsap.fromTo(lineInners, { yPercent: 110 }, {
  yPercent: 0, duration: 0.85, ease: 'power3.out', stagger: 0.12,
  scrollTrigger: { trigger: headline, start: 'top 82%', once: true }
})
```

### 2. Stats counters
Three counters use `gsap.to(obj, { val: TARGET, onUpdate })` with tabular number display. Trigger when the stat row enters viewport.

| Label | Target | Suffix |
|---|---|---|
| MISSIONS COMPLETED | 5000 | + |
| COUNTRIES SERVED | 150 | + |
| AVAILABILITY | 24 | H |

### 3. Marquee ticker
Pure CSS `@keyframes marquee` — duplicate the string twice for a seamless loop. `animation-duration: 28s, linear, infinite`. No JS needed.

### 4. Cards — alternating direction + hover
- Cards 1 & 3: enter `x: -48 → 0`
- Cards 2 & 4: enter `x: 48 → 0`
- Each card gets a numbered index (01–04) in small caps
- CSS hover: `translateY(-6px)`, border goes from `rgba(255,255,255,0.08)` → `rgba(255,255,255,0.22)`, subtle `box-shadow` glow

### 5. Body copy — word stagger
Split the paragraph into `<span>` words, stagger `opacity 0→1` with 0.015s per word via GSAP. Reads as a wave of text materializing.

