# Part 2 — Globe Section (new, after About)

## Library

Install **`react-globe.gl`** (`npm install react-globe.gl`). This is a React wrapper for globe.gl — WebGL-based, supports arc paths between lat/lng coords, marker points, draggable/zoomable interaction, and custom color callbacks.

## Data — flight arcs

10 arcs between luxury destinations:

| Route | From → To |
|---|---|
| Dubai → London | 25.2,55.3 → 51.5,-0.1 |
| Dubai → New York | 25.2,55.3 → 40.7,-74.0 |
| Dubai → Singapore | 25.2,55.3 → 1.3,103.8 |
| London → New York | 51.5,-0.1 → 40.7,-74.0 |
| London → Tokyo | 51.5,-0.1 → 35.7,139.7 |
| New York → Los Angeles | 40.7,-74.0 → 34.0,-118.2 |
| Paris → Dubai | 48.9,2.3 → 25.2,55.3 |
| Tokyo → Sydney | 35.7,139.7 → -33.9,151.2 |
| Singapore → Sydney | 1.3,103.8 → -33.9,151.2 |
| Geneva → New York | 46.2,6.1 → 40.7,-74.0 |

City markers (9 cities): Dubai, London, New York, Singapore, Tokyo, Paris, Geneva, Los Angeles, Sydney.

## Globe styling (dark Aether palette)

```js
globeProps = {
  backgroundColor: 'rgba(0,0,0,0)',      // transparent — section bg shows through
  globeImageUrl: null,                    // no texture — use custom material
  atmosphereColor: '#6aa6ff',             // --sky-deep
  atmosphereAltitude: 0.12,
  // Land polygons from TopoJSON with fill --ink-soft
  // Arc stroke: white → amber (#f4b15c) gradient
  // Arc altitude: 0.25–0.4 (arcs bow outward)
  // Arc dash animated (animateIn)
  // City markers: small white dots + ring pulse animation
}
```

To render land masses without a texture: use `polygonsData` from `world-atlas/countries-110m.json` (tiny, ~120kb).

